dc_title_s: The kingdome of Great Britaine and Ireland
dc_description_s: Relief shown pictorially. Includes text, inset views of London and Edinburgh, Orkney inset, col. ill., and coat-of-arms. Engraved by Jodocus Hondius, 1610. cf. Worms, L. British map engravers. From: The theatre of the empire of Great Britaine ... / divided and described by John Speed. Imprinted at London : anno cum privilegio 1650 are sold by Roger Rea the elder and younger at the Golden Crosse in Cornhill near ye Exchange, [1650]
dc_publisher_s: [London] : Are to be sold by Roger Rea the Elder and younger at the Golden Crosse in Cornhill against the Exchange, [1650]
